The paper presents a novel algorithm for cross-view classification, which involves learning a latent subspace shared by multi-view data. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), multimedia (cs.MM), and neural networks (cs.NE). Given that the paper proposes a new method for multi-view subspace learning, it is most likely to belong to the machine learning and computer vision sub-categories. However, the paper also discusses the use of kernel extensions to boost the representation power of the proposed method, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the artificial intelligence and neural networks sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents experimental results on benchmark datasets, which indicates that it may also be relevant to the multimedia sub-category.
